---
import Base from '../layouts/Base.astro';
import { SITE } from '../consts';
import PriorityLinks from '../components/PriorityLinks.astro';
import { beginnerPriorityLinks } from '../data/priorityLinks';

const jsonLd = {
  '@context': 'https://schema.org', '@type': 'BreadcrumbList', itemListElement: [
    { '@type': 'ListItem', position: 1, name: 'Home', item: SITE.url },
    { '@type': 'ListItem', position: 2, name: 'Beginner guide', item: new URL('/beginner-guide', SITE.url).href },
  ],
};
---
<Base
  title="Moonlight Peaks Beginner Guide: First Week Tips & Early Unlocks"
  description="Moonlight Peaks beginner guide: what to do night one, the vampire farming loop, first quests, magic unlocks, and early progression — confirmed from the live game, not pre-launch guesswork."
  path="/beginner-guide"
  jsonLd={jsonLd}
  crumbs={[{ label: 'Beginner guide' }]}
  showExport
>
  <article class="page">
    <div class="wrap">
      <p class="eyebrow">Entry · Guide</p>
      <h1>Moonlight Peaks <em>beginner guide</em></h1>
      <p class="intro">
        Confirmed from the live game: your first night starts with Orlock handing you Blood Grape
        seeds, registering at Town Hall (where Brook gives you Chester, your living storage bin),
        and a broken wand you'll fix later through story progression. Here's what actually matters
        in your first week. Updated {SITE.updated}.
      </p>

      <div class="callout">
        <strong>Quick answer:</strong> Plant your Blood Grapes right away (5-day grow), register at
        Town Hall for Chester and the <a href="/quests">job board</a>, and don't over-plant early —
        you're watering by hand until magic unlocks Aquaflux. See <a href="/farming">farming</a> for
        the full crop and livestock breakdown.
      </div>

      <h2>Start here checklist</h2>
      <ol class="steps">
        <li><strong>Plant your first Blood Grapes.</strong> Confirmed 5-day grow time — dig with your shovel (no separate hoe) and water every night.</li>
        <li><strong>Register at Town Hall.</strong> Meet Brook, get Chester (your overnight sales bin), and check Albertus' Jobs board for early quests.</li>
        <li><strong>Don't over-plant early.</strong> You're watering by hand until "The Magic of Crops" unlocks Aquaflux — small patches beat an unmanageable field.</li>
        <li><strong>Pick a first focus.</strong> Farming, romance, Nokturna, and magic all connect to their own guide clusters below.</li>
      </ol>

      <PriorityLinks
        title="Beginner pages to open next"
        note="first-session path"
        links={beginnerPriorityLinks}
      />

      <h2>The core loop</h2>
      <p>
        You inherit a run-down family homestead and rebuild it into a cozy-gothic farm. Days revolve
        around tending <strong>mystical crops</strong>, raising <strong>magical livestock</strong>,
        and using magic — controlled watering cans and spells — to work the land. Unusually for the
        genre, farming leans into the night, which suits your vampire lifestyle.
      </p>

      <h2>What you'll be doing</h2>
      <ul>
        <li><strong>Farming & livestock</strong> — grow enchanted crops and raise creatures unique to the town.</li>
        <li><strong>Spells & potions</strong> — study witchcraft to help on the farm and when gathering.</li>
        <li><strong>Fishing & foraging</strong> — classic cozy gathering, with a supernatural twist.</li>
        <li><strong>Cooking</strong> — turn your harvest into meals and brews.</li>
        <li><strong>Embroidery & flower arranging</strong> — slower hobby activities, shown in the demo.</li>
        <li><strong>Nokturna</strong> — collect cards and play the town's favorite game against residents.</li>
        <li><strong>Home design</strong> — decorate a gothic cottage (pick the perfect coffin) and develop your property.</li>
      </ul>

      <h2>Being a vampire</h2>
      <p>
        Your lineage is a toolkit, not just a theme. You can <strong>shapeshift</strong> — turning
        into a bat to cross town quickly and reach hidden areas — and unlock ancient abilities from
        enhanced senses onward as you progress. There's a mines area to explore, but note there's
        <strong>no combat anywhere</strong>, so it stays cozy. Many residents are supernatural too,
        so you blend right in.
      </p>

      <h2>The town & its people</h2>
      <p>
        Moonlight Peaks is home to seven families across humans and creatures of the night —
        werewolves, witches, mermaids, and more, with Death himself among the notable characters.
        Befriending and romancing them is a central pillar; our
        <a href="/romance">romance & families entry</a> tracks all 23 confirmed romance candidates
        and their gift preferences as we verify them.
      </p>

      <h2>What's still being verified</h2>
      <p>
        Most core systems are confirmed and documented across this site — night-farming, magic
        unlocks, quests, and the seven families are all live-game data at this point. What's still
        catching up: a complete gift table for every resident (only a few are fully confirmed so
        far), the full Nokturna card list, and exact crop sale prices. We label each of these
        clearly rather than guessing, and update them as real data comes in.
      </p>

      <h2>Best next pages by goal</h2>
      <table class="facts">
        <tr><th>If you're just starting out</th><td><a href="/quests">Quests</a>, <a href="/known-issues">known issues</a>, and <a href="/platforms">platform guide</a></td></tr>
        <tr><th>If you want romance</th><td><a href="/romance">Romance guide</a>, <a href="/characters">characters</a>, and <a href="/characters/saga">Saga</a></td></tr>
        <tr><th>If you want farming</th><td><a href="/farming">Farming guide</a>, <a href="/magic">magic</a>, and <a href="/activities">activities</a></td></tr>
        <tr><th>If you want collecting</th><td><a href="/activities/fishing">fishing</a>, <a href="/activities/foraging">foraging</a>, <a href="/locations">locations</a>, and the <a href="/map">map</a></td></tr>
      </table>

      <div class="callout wip">
        Post-launch entry, updated as we verify more. A few things are still incomplete — full
        crop prices, complete gift tables, and the full Nokturna card list — and we label those
        clearly rather than guessing. Spot something to add? Email {SITE.contact}.
      </div>
    </div>
  </article>
</Base>
